<h1><%= @document.title %></h1>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h3>File Information</h3>
    <p><strong>Filename:</strong> <%= @document.file.filename %></p>
    <p><strong>File Size:</strong> <%= number_to_human_size(@document.file.byte_size) %></p>
    <p><strong>Content Type:</strong> <%= @document.file.content_type %></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row mt-4">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h3>ActiveStorage URL Analysis</h3>
    <p class="text-muted">You can use these URLs to verify the behavior of ActiveStorage signed URLs and public-read buckets.</p>
    
    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="card-header">
        <h5 class="card-title">1. Regular Signed URL (Default)</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <code><%= @signed_url %></code>
        <br><br>
        <a href="<%= @signed_url %>" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">Access Signed URL</a>
        <small class="text-muted d-block mt-2">※ This is ActiveStorage's default behavior</small>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="card-header">
        <h5 class="card-title">2. Expiring Signed URL (Expires in 1 second)</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <code><%= @signed_url_expires_in %></code>
        <br><br>
        <a href="<%= @signed_url_expires_in %>" target="_blank" class="btn btn-warning">Access Expiring URL</a>
        <small class="text-muted d-block mt-2">※ Should return 403 error after 1 second</small>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="card-header">
        <h5 class="card-title">3. Public URL (Without query parameters)</h5>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <code><%= @public_url %></code>
        <br><br>
        <a href="<%= @public_url %>" target="_blank" class="btn btn-success">Access Public URL</a>
        <small class="text-muted d-block mt-2">※ Should be accessible via this URL because the bucket is public-read</small>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row mt-4">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h3>Experiment Procedure</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Click "Access Signed URL" → File is accessible (200 OK)</li>
      <li>Click "Access Expiring URL" → Immediately accessible</li>
      <li>Wait a moment and click "Access Expiring URL" → Returns 403 Forbidden</li>
      <li>Click "Access Public URL" → File is accessible (200 OK, because bucket is public-read)</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-info">※ This experiment allows you to verify the behavior of ActiveStorage's signed URL functionality and public-read buckets.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
  <%= link_to 'Back to Documents', documents_path, class: 'btn btn-secondary' %>
</div>
